# NOTION MEMORY BANK - PAGE LOCATIONS

**CRITICAL:** This project uses **Notion** as the Memory Bank backend. All read/write operations MUST use Notion MCP tools (`notion-fetch`, `notion-update-page`, `notion-create-pages`), NOT local file operations.

**Language:** All content written to Notion (page body, properties, subtasks, etc.) MUST be in **English**. Chat responses to the user may use the user's language.

## Identifier Convention

- **Projects**: `projectId` in config matches the **Project ID** property in the **Projects** database (numeric value). In JSON you may use a **number** (`123`) or **string** (`"123"`) — both are valid.
- **Tasks**: `taskId` matches **Task ID** (same rule: JSON number or string).

Example: `projectId` `123` or `"123"` → resolve via **Project ID**; `taskId` `588` or `"588"` → resolve via **Task ID**.

**MCP / search:** When passing `projectId` or `taskId` to `notion-search` `query` (or comparing to Notion properties), coerce if needed (e.g. `String(projectId)`) so the value matches Notion’s stored form.

## Configuration

Read `.cursor/notion-memory-bank.json`:

**Config write format (MUST):** When writing `.cursor/notion-memory-bank.json`, use formatted JSON: 2-space indentation, one key per line. Parse existing content, merge changes, then serialize with `JSON.stringify(obj, null, 2)` – never minified single-line JSON.

**Migration:** Existing configs without the new keys (productContextPageId, systemPatternsPageId, techContextPageId, styleGuidePageId, projectName, taskName, issueId) work as-is; missing keys are treated as null. Subpages are created on first use when notion-verification runs (e.g. `/van`). projectName and taskName are populated when notion-verification fetches Project and Task pages.

| Key | Required | Description |
|-----|----------|-------------|
| projectId | Yes | Numeric key: JSON **number** or **string** (e.g. `123` or `"123"`) — must match **Project ID** on the Project row |
| projectName | No | Page title of Project (populated when notion-verification fetches Project) |
| taskId | No* | Numeric key: JSON **number** or **string** (e.g. `588` or `"588"`) — must match **Task ID** on the Task row; null → `/van [description]` creates one |
| taskName | No | Page title of Task (populated when notion-verification fetches Task) |
| issueId | No | Jira/issue ID from Task's "Issue ID" property (synced when notion-verification fetches Task) |
| projectsDataSourceUrl | Yes | Projects data source (`collection://...` from `notion-fetch` of the Projects **database**). If invalid, recover per `Core/notion-memory-bank-ops.mdc` (**Recover invalid or missing data source URLs**) |
| tasksDataSourceUrl | Yes | Tasks data source (`collection://...` from `notion-fetch` of the Tasks **database**). Same recovery if invalid |
| activeContextPageId | No | activeContext subpage ID; if null, create under Project |
| progressPageId | No | progress subpage ID; if null, create under Project |
| productContextPageId | No | productContext subpage ID; if null, create under Project (Level 4) |
| systemPatternsPageId | No | systemPatterns subpage ID; if null, create under Project (Level 4) |
| techContextPageId | No | techContext subpage ID; if null, create under Project (Level 4) |
| styleGuidePageId | No | style-guide subpage ID; if null, create under Project (creative UI/UX) |
| creativePageId | No | Creative subpage ID; if null, create under Task |
| reflectionPageId | No | Reflection subpage ID; if null, create under Task |
| archivePageId | No | Archive subpage ID; if null, create under Task |

## Subpage Naming Convention

- **Project subpages** (activeContext, progress, productContext, systemPatterns, techContext, style-guide): Include `projectId` in title. Format: `Active Context <projectId>`, `Progress <projectId>`, etc. (e.g. `Active Context 37` whether `projectId` is `37` or `"37"`). Analogous to Task subpages including taskId. Enables stale detection when page is not under the expected Project.
- **Task subpages** (creative, reflection, archive): Include `taskId` in title. Format: `Creative <taskId>`, `Reflection <taskId>`, `Archive <taskId>` (e.g. `Creative 1391`). Enables stale detection when page is not under the expected Task.

## Resolving Page IDs

1. **Project (by projectId)**: Search by **Project ID** first (`userDefined:Project ID`). Use `notion-query-database-view` with a view filtered by **Project ID** when available; otherwise `notion-search` with `data_source_url` = `projectsDataSourceUrl`, `query` = string form of `projectId` (e.g. `String(projectId)` if the tool expects a string). Verify the result's **Project ID** matches (normalize number vs string when comparing); then `notion-fetch` with page URL.
2. **Task (by taskId)**: Search by **Task ID** first (`userDefined:Task ID`). Same pattern: `query` = string form of `taskId` if needed; verify **Task ID** matches `taskId`. **Note:** If your Tasks database still uses a property named **ID** (not **Task ID**), the MCP key may be `userDefined:ID` — confirm on a `notion-fetch` of a Task row; values are numeric like **Project ID**.
3. **Subpages**: Use explicit page IDs if set; otherwise create under Project or Task with `notion-create-pages`.

**Identifier is source of truth:** If projectId or taskId cannot be resolved (no matching result), report verification incomplete. Do NOT use projectName/taskName as fallback. See `Core/notion-verification.mdc` step 4.

**Bad data source URLs:** If `projectsDataSourceUrl` / `tasksDataSourceUrl` fail, run recovery in `Core/notion-memory-bank-ops.mdc` before relying on scoped search. See `Core/notion-verification.mdc` step 2.

